Title: A GENERAL DESCENT FRAMEWORK FOR THE MONOTONE VARIATIONAL INEQUALITY PROBLEM  
Author: JIA HAO WU MICHAEL FLORIAN PATRICE MARCOTTE 
Keyword: Key words Variational Inequalities, Descent methods, Optimization.  
Date: 1993  
Address: Montreal  
Affiliation: Centre de recherche sur les transports Universite de  
Abstract: We present a framework for descent algorithms that solve the monotone variational inequality problem V IP v which consists in finding a solution v 2 v which satisfies s(v) T (uv) 0, for all u 2 v . This unified framework includes, as special cases, some well known iterative methods and equivalent optimization formulations. A descent method is developed for an equivalent general optimization formulation and a proof of its convergence is given. Based on this unified algorithmic framework, we show that a variant of the descent method where each subproblem is only solved approximately is globally convergent under certain conditions. 
